SUCCESS_RESET_CONTENT.name: SUCCESS_RESET_CONTENT
SUCCESS_RESET_CONTENT.comment: The server has fulfilled the request and the user agent SHOULD reset the document view which caused the request to be sent. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.2.6">205 Reset Content</a>

SUCCESS_PARTIAL_CONTENT.name: SUCCESS_PARTIAL_CONTENT
SUCCESS_PARTIAL_CONTENT.comment: The server has fulfilled the partial GET request for the resource. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.2.7">206 Partial Content</a>

SUCCESS_NON_AUTHORITATIVE_INFORMATION.name: SUCCESS_NON_AUTHORITATIVE_INFORMATION
SUCCESS_NON_AUTHORITATIVE_INFORMATION.comment: The returned metainformation in the entity-header is not the definitive set as available from the origin server, but is gatheredfrom a local or a third-party copy. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.2.4">203 Non-Authoritative Information</a>

SUCCESS_NO_CONTENT.name: SUCCESS_NO_CONTENT
SUCCESS_NO_CONTENT.comment: The server has fulfilled the request but does not need to return an entity-body, and might want to return updated metainformation. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.2.5">204 No Content</a>

SUCCESS_MULTI_STATUS.name: SUCCESS_MULTI_STATUS
SUCCESS_MULTI_STATUS.comment: Multiple resources were to be affected by the COPY, but errors on some of them prevented the operation from taking place. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4918#section-11.1">207 Multi-Status</a>

SUCCESS_IM_USED.name: SUCCESS_IM_USED
SUCCESS_IM_USED.comment: The response is a representation of the result of one or more instance-manipulations applied to the current instance. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3229#section-10.4.1">226 IM Used</a>

SUCCESS_CREATED.name: SUCCESS_CREATED
SUCCESS_CREATED.comment: The request has been fulfilled and resulted in a new resource being created. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.2.2">201 Created</a>

SUCCESS_ACCEPTED.name: SUCCESS_ACCEPTED
SUCCESS_ACCEPTED.comment: The request has been accepted for processing, but the processing has not been completed. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.2.3">202 Accepted</a>

SERVER_ERROR_VARIANT_ALSO_NEGOTIATES.name: SERVER_ERROR_VARIANT_ALSO_NEGOTIATES
SERVER_ERROR_VARIANT_ALSO_NEGOTIATES.comment: The server has an internal configuration error: the chosen variant resource is configured to engage in transparent content negotiation itself, and is therefore not a proper end point in the negotiation process. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2295#section-8.1">506 Variant Also Negotiates</a>

SERVER_ERROR_SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE.name: SERVER_ERROR_SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE
SERVER_ERROR_SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE.comment: The server is currently unable to handle the request due to a temporary overloading or maintenance of the server. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.5.4">503 Service Unavailable</a>

SERVER_ERROR_NOT_IMPLEMENTED.name: SERVER_ERROR_NOT_IMPLEMENTED
SERVER_ERROR_NOT_IMPLEMENTED.comment: The server does not support the functionality required to fulfill the request. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.5.2">501 Not Implemented</a>

SERVER_ERROR_NOT_EXTENDED.name: SERVER_ERROR_NOT_EXTENDED
SERVER_ERROR_NOT_EXTENDED.comment: The policy for accessing the resource has not been met in the request. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2774#section-7">510 Not Extended </a>

SERVER_ERROR_LOOP_DETECTED.name: SERVER_ERROR_LOOP_DETECTED
SERVER_ERROR_LOOP_DETECTED.comment: The server terminated an operation because it encountered an infinite loop while processing the request. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5842#section-7.2">508 Loop Detected</a>

SERVER_ERROR_INTERNAL.name: SERVER_ERROR_INTERNAL
SERVER_ERROR_INTERNAL.comment: The server encountered an unexpected condition which prevented it from fulfilling the request. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.5.1">500 Internal Server Error</a>

SERVER_ERROR_INSUFFICIENT_STORAGE.name: SERVER_ERROR_INSUFFICIENT_STORAGE
SERVER_ERROR_INSUFFICIENT_STORAGE.comment: The method could not be performed on the resource because the server is unable to store the representation needed to successfully complete the request. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4918#section-11.5">507 Insufficient Storage</a>

SERVER_ERROR_HTTP_VERSION_NOT_SUPPORTED.name: SERVER_ERROR_HTTP_VERSION_NOT_SUPPORTED
SERVER_ERROR_HTTP_VERSION_NOT_SUPPORTED.comment: The server does not support, or refuses to support, the HTTP protocol version that was used in the request message. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.5.6">505 HTTP Version Not Supported</a>

SERVER_ERROR_GATEWAY_TIMEOUT.name: SERVER_ERROR_GATEWAY_TIMEOUT
SERVER_ERROR_GATEWAY_TIMEOUT.comment: The server, while acting as a gateway or proxy, did not receive a timely response from the upstream server specified by the URI (e.g. HTTP, FTP, LDAP) or some other auxiliary server (e.g. DNS) it needed to access in attempting to complete the request. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.5.5">504 Gateway Timeout</a>

SERVER_ERROR_BAD_GATEWAY.name: SERVER_ERROR_BAD_GATEWAY
SERVER_ERROR_BAD_GATEWAY.comment: The server, while acting as a gateway or proxy, received an invalid response from the upstream server it accessed in attempting to fulfill the request. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.5.3">502 Bad Gateway</a>

REDIRECTION_USE_PROXY.name: REDIRECTION_USE_PROXY
REDIRECTION_USE_PROXY.comment: The requested resource MUST be accessed through the proxy given by the Location field. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.3.6">305 Use Proxy</a>

REDIRECTION_TEMPORARY_REDIRECT.name: REDIRECTION_TEMPORARY_REDIRECT
REDIRECTION_TEMPORARY_REDIRECT.comment: The requested resource resides temporarily under a different URI. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.3.8">307 Temporary Redirect</a>

REDIRECTION_SEE_OTHER.name: REDIRECTION_SEE_OTHER
REDIRECTION_SEE_OTHER.comment: The response to the request can be found under a different URI and SHOULD be retrieved using a GET method on that resource. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.3.4">303 See Other</a>

REDIRECTION_NOT_MODIFIED.name: REDIRECTION_NOT_MODIFIED
REDIRECTION_NOT_MODIFIED.comment: The response to the request has not been modified since the conditions indicated by the client's conditional GET request. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.3.5">304 Not Modified</a>

REDIRECTION_MULTIPLE_CHOICES.name: REDIRECTION_MULTIPLE_CHOICES
REDIRECTION_MULTIPLE_CHOICES.comment: The requested resource corresponds to any one of a set of representations, each with its own specific location, and agent-driven negotiation information is being provided so that the user (or user agent) can select a preferred representation and redirect its request to that location. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.3.1">300 Multiple Choices</a>

REDIRECTION_MOVED_PERMANENTLY.name: REDIRECTION_MOVED_PERMANENTLY
REDIRECTION_MOVED_PERMANENTLY.comment: The requested resource has been assigned a new permanent URI and any future references to this resource SHOULD use one of the returned URIs. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.3.2">310 Moved Permanently</a>

REDIRECTION_FOUND.name: REDIRECTION_FOUND
REDIRECTION_FOUND.comment: The requested resource resides temporarily under a different URI. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.3.3">302 Found</a>

INFORMATIONAL_SWITCHING_PROTOCOLS.name: INFORMATIONAL_SWITCHING_PROTOCOLS
INFORMATIONAL_SWITCHING_PROTOCOLS.comment: The server understands and is willing to comply with the client's request for a change in the application protocol being used on this connection. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.1.2">101 Switching Protocols</a>

INFORMATIONAL_PROCESSING.name: INFORMATIONAL_PROCESSING
INFORMATIONAL_PROCESSING.comment: The server has accepted the complete request, but has not yet completed it. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2518#section-10.1">102 Processing</a>

INFORMATIONAL_CONTINUE.name: INFORMATIONAL_CONTINUE
INFORMATIONAL_CONTINUE.comment: The client SHOULD continue with its request. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.1.1">100 Continue</a>

CLIENT_ERROR_UPGRADE_REQUIRED.name: CLIENT_ERROR_UPGRADE_REQUIRED
CLIENT_ERROR_UPGRADE_REQUIRED.comment: Allows a server to definitively state the precise protocol extensions given resource must be served with. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2817#section-6">426 Upgrade Required</a>

CLIENT_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_MEDIA_TYPE.name: CLIENT_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_MEDIA_TYPE
CLIENT_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_MEDIA_TYPE.comment: The server is refusing to service the request because the entity of the request is in a format not supported by the requested resource for the requested method. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.4.16">415 Unsupported Media Type</a>

CLIENT_ERROR_UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY.name: CLIENT_ERROR_UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY
CLIENT_ERROR_UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY.comment: The server understands the content type of the request entity, and the syntax of the request entity is correct but was unable to process the contained instructions. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4918#section-11.2">422 Unprocessable Entity</a>

CLIENT_ERROR_REQUESTED_RANGE_NOT_SATISFI.name: CLIENT_ERROR_REQUESTED_RANGE_NOT_SATISFIABLE
CLIENT_ERROR_REQUESTED_RANGE_NOT_SATISFI.comment: Request included a Range request-header field, and none of the range-specifier values in this field overlap the current extent of the selected resource. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.4.17">416 Requested Range Not Satisfiable</a>

CLIENT_ERROR_REQUEST_URI_TOO_LONG.name: CLIENT_ERROR_REQUEST_URI_TOO_LONG
CLIENT_ERROR_REQUEST_URI_TOO_LONG.comment: The server is refusing to service the request because the Request-URI is longer than the server is willing to interpret. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.4.15">414 Request-URI Too Long</a>

CLIENT_ERROR_REQUEST_TIMEOUT.name: CLIENT_ERROR_REQUEST_TIMEOUT
CLIENT_ERROR_REQUEST_TIMEOUT.comment: The client did not produce a request within the time that the server was prepared to wait. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.4.9">408 Request Timeout</a>

CLIENT_ERROR_REQUEST_ENTITY_TOO_LARGE.name: CLIENT_ERROR_REQUEST_ENTITY_TOO_LARGE
CLIENT_ERROR_REQUEST_ENTITY_TOO_LARGE.comment: The server is refusing to process a request because the request entity is larger than the server is willing or able to process. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.4.14">413 Request Entity Too Large</a>

CLIENT_ERROR_PRECONDITION_FAILED.name: CLIENT_ERROR_PRECONDITION_FAILED
CLIENT_ERROR_PRECONDITION_FAILED.comment: The precondition given in one or more of the request-header fields evaluated to false when it was tested on the server. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.4.13">412 Precondition Failed</a>

CLIENT_ERROR_NOT_FOUND.name: CLIENT_ERROR_NOT_FOUND
CLIENT_ERROR_NOT_FOUND.comment: The server has not found anything matching the Request-URI. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.4.5">404 Not Found</a>

CLIENT_ERROR_NOT_ACCEPTABLE.name: CLIENT_ERROR_NOT_ACCEPTABLE
CLIENT_ERROR_NOT_ACCEPTABLE.comment: The resource identified by the request is only capable of generating response entities which have content characteristics not acceptable according to the accept headers sent in the request. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.4.7">406 Not Acceptable</a>

CLIENT_ERROR_METHOD_NOT_ALLOWED.name: CLIENT_ERROR_METHOD_NOT_ALLOWED
CLIENT_ERROR_METHOD_NOT_ALLOWED.comment: The method specified in the Request-Line is not allowed for the resource identified by the Request-URI. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.4.6">405 Method Not Allowed</a>

CLIENT_ERROR_LOCKED.name: CLIENT_ERROR_LOCKED
CLIENT_ERROR_LOCKED.comment: The source or destination resource of a method is locked. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4918#section-11.3">423 Locked</a>

CLIENT_ERROR_LENGTH_REQUIRED.name: CLIENT_ERROR_LENGTH_REQUIRED
CLIENT_ERROR_LENGTH_REQUIRED.comment: The server refuses to accept the request without a defined Content-Length. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.4.12">411 Length Required</a>

CLIENT_ERROR_GONE.name: CLIENT_ERROR_GONE
CLIENT_ERROR_GONE.comment: The requested resource is no longer available at the server and no forwarding address is known. This condition is expected to be considered permanent. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.4.11">410 Gone</a>

CLIENT_ERROR_FORBIDDEN.name: CLIENT_ERROR_FORBIDDEN
CLIENT_ERROR_FORBIDDEN.comment: The server understood the request, but is refusing to authorize it. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.4.4">403 Bad Request</a>

CLIENT_ERROR_FAILED_DEPENDENCY.name: CLIENT_ERROR_FAILED_DEPENDENCY
CLIENT_ERROR_FAILED_DEPENDENCY.comment: The method could not be performed on the resource because the requested action depended on another action and that action failed. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4918#section-11.4">424 Failed Dependency</a>

CLIENT_ERROR_EXPECTATION_FAILED.name: CLIENT_ERROR_EXPECTATION_FAILED
CLIENT_ERROR_EXPECTATION_FAILED.comment: The expectation given in an Expect request-header field could not be met by this server. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.4.18">417 Expectation Failed</a>

CLIENT_ERROR_CONFLICT.name: CLIENT_ERROR_CONFLICT
CLIENT_ERROR_CONFLICT.comment: The request could not be completed due to a conflict with the current state of the resource. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.4.10">409 Conflict</a>

CLIENT_ERROR_BAD_REQUEST.name: CLIENT_ERROR_BAD_REQUEST
CLIENT_ERROR_BAD_REQUEST.comment: The request could not be understood by the server due to malformed syntax. @see <a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-p2-semantics-17#section-7.4.1">400 Bad Request</a>
